Battlefield Wiki is a comprehensive database focusing on the Battlefield video game series. The wiki is dedicated to collecting all information related to the franchise.

items.name: Φρικηπαίδεια
items.title: Φρικηπαίδεια
items.desc: Η Φρικηπαίδεια αποτελεί μια ελεύθερη συνεργατική εγκυκλοπαίδεια, καταγραφή της ανθρώπινης, Κτηνώδους Δύναμης Ωγκώδους Άγνοιας (ΚΔΩΑ), δηλαδή η απόλυτη συνεισφορά στην ανθρώπινη μπούρδα. Εδώ θα βρείτε πληροφορίες που δεν υπάρχουν πουθενά αλλού. Τολμάμε να γράφουμε πληροφορίες που δε γράφει κανείς άλλος. Παντού θα βρείτε για παράδειγμα να λένε, ότι τα μπαλάκια του γκολφ είναι άσπρα. Κανείς όμως δε γράφει πληροφορίες, όπως σε τι οικοσυστήματα συναντώνται, ή, με τι τρέφονται. Κανείς άλλος δεν παρέχει τόση παραπληροφόρηση με τόσο «πληροφοριακό» τρόπο. Κάτι δηλαδή σαν την πολιτική, μόνο που είναι γραμμένη με χιούμορ. Μάλιστα, είμαστε τόσο επιτυχημένοι σε αυτό που κάνουμε, που έχουμε αποκτήσει και παρωδία της εκλεπτυσμένης αυτής σελίδας.

We are currently editing 1,222 articles since March 15th, 2006 and you can help!

items.name: Star Wars Battlefront Wiki
items.title: Star Wars Battlefront Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Star Wars Battlefront Wiki!
items.desc:
Are you new to Star Wars Battlefront series, or a Veteran? No matter who you are and your role, we welcome you to the community! Learn about strategies to conquer maps; or if you are sneaky, feel free to learn about glitches from Bespin: Cloud City to Yavin 4: Temple! Discover some glitch or strategy that no one knows about? Give in your share! Our friendly staff will find a way to help you through your time with us, whether you are new to Wikia, or just need a social wiki to spend your time. We always have a set of watchful eyes for unpleasant personnel.

Due to a growing number of Mod community, we have our share, and trying our best to give you what we know from mods we have tried. Just want to find a fellow group of Battlefrontians to rely on to give hints, our wiki is the right place! Our different time zone Admin ensures a near 24/7 service to those that need help! But you are probably tired of these summery, go come to the website and find out for yourself! See you there!

items.name: Freeciv
items.title: Freeciv
items.headline: Welcome to the Freeciv Wiki!
items.desc:
The Freeciv Wiki is dedicated to Freeciv, which is a Free and Open Source empire-building strategy game inspired by the history of human civilization. The game commences in prehistory and your mission is to lead your tribe from the Stone Age to the Space Age...

Freeciv is much much more than a game: In Freeciv the game players can decide what the rules will be! This means that unlike nearly every other computer game, Freeciv can be a different game each time you play. This opportunity comes with some cost. Especially at first, a player trying to tackle all the subtleties and nuances of this complex gaming experience can get a little lost. 

We welcome new users to contribute to and edit the wiki!

items.name: Wikigrounds, the free Newgrounds encyclopedia
items.title: Wikigrounds, the free Newgrounds encyclopedia
items.headline: Wikigrounds, the Newgrounds Encyclopedia
items.desc: Newgrounds is the oldest, largest, and most prestigious Flash Portal in history. Since its origins in 1995, it has been the source of some of the most notable material on the internet, as a place where creators share their work with fans and each other. Learn about its games, movies, culture, and history on Wikigrounds.

items.name: San Francisco Homeless Resource
items.title: San Francisco Homeless Resource
items.headline: Welcome to the San Francisco Homeless Resource Wiki!
items.desc:
San Francisco Homeless Resource is a collaborative website for homeless advocates, providers, government and others in San Francisco. The wiki is a new evolution of how all parties helping the homeless can get together and share information efficiently and quickly.

The site can be updated by any user, so everyone can add and update information -- allowing much greater efficiency in serving the homeless community in San Francisco.

items.name: Freeciv.org ジャパン
items.title: Freeciv.org ジャパン
items.headline: Civilizationライクな戦略シミュレーションゲーム「Freeciv」へようこそ！
items.desc:
『Freeciv』 はフリーのターン制多人数戦略ゲームです。 各プレイヤーはある一つの文明 (civilization) の指導者になり、 次の最終目標を目指して戦います。このコミュニティーでは『Freeciv』のマニュアル、ユニット、地形などゲームに関する情報を載せています。まだまだ情報が必要ですので皆様からの編集を歓迎します。

このコミュニティーで下記のことをすることができます。 
1、情報を編集することができます。
2、情報を提供することができます。
3、仲間を見つけてフォーラムで話したりすることが可能です。
4、仲間とチャットをすることもできます。

編集作業を行う場合はぜひぜひ、アカウントを登録してログインして下さい。

items.name: Imagination Companions, A Foster's Home for Imaginary Friends Wiki
items.title: Imagination Companions, A Foster's Home for Imaginary Friends Wiki
items.headline: Visit the Imagination Companions Wiki
items.desc:
Welcome to Imagination Companions, the Wikia about the Cartoon Network series Foster's Home for Imaginary Friends.

The series, which premiered on August 12th, 2004, is about a place where imaginary friends go to be adopted after being left behind by children who have outgrown them.

The home's founder is dear old, lovable Madame Foster, and contains many wacky residents. Leading the way is Blooregard Q. Kazoo (a/k/a "Bloo" for short), who along with his creator, Mac, join other imaginary friends like Wilt, a one-armed basketball player; Eduardo, who protects those from everything but is scared of even houseflies; the sanity-challenged Coco, created by a stranded child as a companion as a hybrid of a bird, an airplane and a tree; the stuffy Mr. Herriman, an amorphized rabbit who still lives in the Edwardian era, and Madame Foster's human granddaughter, the overworked and lovable Frankie, who takes care of everyone.

Other friends that have been part of the residence are Fluffer Nutter, a pink squirrel; The New Guy, who once took ofense to Bloo's sense of humor (or so it seems); one imaginary Prince Charming, who used lame pick-up lines on Frankie when he first arrived; and Jackie Khones, a green one-eyed stick figure with a deep voice.

items.name: Wiki Wakfu

En plus du jeu en ligne, elle se compose d'un jeu vidéo Xbox Live Arcade (Islands of Wakfu), une série télévisée éponyme, des comics/mangas, un jeu de cartes à collectionner, des figurines et plus.

Wakfu se déroule dans le même univers fantastique que le jeu vidéo Dofus (aussi d'Ankama Games) mais approximativement 1000 ans plus tard, après qu'un évènement catastrophique connu sous le nom de Grand déluge s'est produit.

The Super Friends roster consisted of a core group of characters central to the spirit of comic book heroism: Superman, Batman, Robin, Aquaman and Wonder Woman. Throughout the different seasons, they began to include other DC Comics characters such as the Flash, Green Lantern and Hawkman. Enter now to learn more about SuperFriends!

items.name: Fruits Basket Wiki
items.title: Fruits Basket Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Fruits Basket Wiki and Database!
items.desc: Fruits Basket (sometimes abbreviated Furuba) is a Japanese manga series by Natsuki Takaya. It was serialized in the semi-monthly Japanese magazine Hana to Yume, published by Hakusensha, from 1999 to 2006. The series was also adapted into a 26-episode anime series, directed by Akitaro Daichi. The series tells the story of Tohru Honda, an orphan girl who, after meeting Yuki, Kyo, and Shigure Sohma, learns that thirteen members of the Sohma family are possessed by the animals of the Chinese zodiac and are cursed to turn into their animal forms if they embrace anyone of the opposite sex. The name was derived from a popular children's game, called Fruits Basket.

items.name: Rule of Rose Wiki
items.title: Rule of Rose Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Rule of Rose Wiki!
items.desc:
Rule of Rose is a survival horror game for the PlayStation 2 developed by Punchline and published by Atlus in 2006. It has often been compared with other similar survival horror gaming series such as Silent Hill and Clock Tower, due to the psychological horror elements used throughout, and its distorted storyline. It is also compared to the one-shot game, Haunting Ground due to the use of a canine companion for the main character.
Set in 1930, Cardington, Bedfordshire, England, a few years before the second World War broke out, the game tells the story of a teenage girl named Jennifer as she is forced to work for the Red Crayon Aristocrat Club: an unruly, cruel society formed by the children of the Rose Garden Orphanage.

items.name: Fatal Frame Wiki

items.desc: The Fatal Frame Wikia is a community site dedicated to the Fatal Frame series of survival horror video games. Come explore our content and help us expand this database... or join us in discussion about the characters, the gameplay, or the subject matter in general. All are welcome!

items.desc:

La série est mondialement connue et dépeint le stéréotype de la famille américaine moyenne.
Elle a été adaptée en long métrage et en jeux vidéo et a été déclinée en de nombreux produits dérivés.

La famille Halliwell est une longue lignée de sorciers qui se transmettent un grimoire  de génération en génération, Le Livre des Ombres. Unies par le « Pouvoir des Trois », les sœurs Halliwell utilisent leurs pouvoirs surnaturels pour combattre les sorciers, démons et autres forces maléfiques qui peuplent la ville de San Francisco en Californie.

items.name: FringeWiki
items.title: FringeWiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Fringe Wiki!
items.desc: Fringe is a television series developed by J.J. Abrams for FOX. It is the fourth series co-created by Abrams (Felicity, Alias, Lost) and also his fourth collaboration with co-creators Roberto Orci and Alex Kurtzman. It is produced by Bad Robot in association with Warner Bros. Television. The plot deals with a research scientist named Walter Bishop (who Orci describes as "Frankenstein mixed with Albert Einstein"), his son, and a female FBI agent who brings them back together. The show is described as a cross between The X-Files, Altered States, and The Twilight Zone. The series premiered on September 9, 2008 at 8:00 p.m. ET on FOX. A pre-air version of the pilot was screened in its entirety for fans at Comic-Con 2008. The television show has spawned a series of comic books and novels that expand on the mythology of the series.

items.name: Wikianswers - Frag Wikia!
items.title: Wikianswers - Frag Wikia!
items.headline: Löchere die Frag Wikia Community mit deinen Fragen
items.desc:
Wikianswers - Frag Wikia! ist ein Projekt von Wikia. Unser Ziel ist Erstellung und Organisation von freiem Wissen.

Das Ziel von Wikianswers ist die gemeinschaftliche Erarbeitung der besten Antworten auf jede Frage. Dazu sollen möglichst viele Fakten angegeben werden, die aus öffentlich verfügbaren Quellen recherchiert wurden.

Wikianswers - Frag Wikia! ist eine Frage-Antwort-Seite, die durch die traditionellen Wiki-Prinzipien Offenheit, Transparenz und Editierbarkeit geprägt ist. Aus diesem Grund steht der komplette Inhalt von Wikianswers unter der GNU-Lizenz für freie Dokumentation (GFDL). Das bedeutet, dass er von Dritten frei weiterverwendet werden kann, wobei das Urheberrecht natürlich weiterhin bei den Originalautoren der Antworten liegt.

Jeder kann sich an Wikianswers beteiligen - sogar wenn er nicht angemeldet ist. Auch ist es durchaus erwünscht, unvollständig oder unverständlich gestellte Fragen umzuformulieren und sinnentstellende Schreibfehler zu beseitigen.

items.headline: Cut Enemies Down at the Afro Samurai Wikia!
items.desc: Afro Samurai (アフロサムライ Afuro Samurai?), also written AFRO SAMURAI, is a Japanese seinen dōjinshi manga series written and illustrated by manga artist Takashi Okazaki. It was originally serialized irregularly in the avant-garde dōjinshi manga magazine Nou Nou Hau from September 1999 to May 2000. Inspired by Takashi Okazaki's love of soul and hip hop music and American media, Afro Samurai follows the life of Afro Samurai who witnessed his father (owner of the No. 1 headband) being killed by a gunslinger, Justice (owner of the No. 2 headband) while he was a child. As an adult, Afro sets off to avenge his father's death and kill Justice.

items.name: Fringe
items.title: Fringe
items.headline: Willkommen im Fringe Wiki - Grenzfälle des FBI -
items.desc:
Willkommen im Wiki zu unserer Lieblings-Serie Fringe! Die FBI-Agentin Olivia Dunham geht zusammen mit dem Kleinganoven Peter Bishop und dessen verrücktem Vater Dr. Walter Bishop mysteriösen Vorfällen auf den Grund. Teleportation, Mutation, Telekinese, Pyrokinese und sogar Zeitreisen gehören zu dem sogenanntem Schema, welches aufgeklärt werden soll. 
Die Mystery-Crime-Serie handelt von einer Spezialabteilung des FBI, die sich anfangs mit Vorkommnissen später " Fringe-Fälle" genannt  beschäftigt, die sich nicht mit herkömmlichen wissenschaftlichen Methoden erklären oder lösen lassen. Im Laufe der Serie wird jedoch klar, dass eine mysteriöse New Yorker Technologie-Firma, Massive Dynamic immer öfter in die Fälle verwickelt ist, und deren zwielichtige Machenschaften mit einem Paralleluniversum verbunden sind.
Extrem spannend und kurzweilig.

items.desc: The Friday Night Lights Wiki is a community run fan site that celebrates the Peter Berg book as well as its' popular NBC series and movies.
